 {"id":"bd-14i","title":"Implement FastMCP theme system","description":"# Implement FastMCP Theme System

## Purpose
Define a cohesive visual identity for FastMCP that creates a premium, professional appearance. The theme system provides consistent colors, styles, and visual language across all rich output. This is the "brand" of FastMCP's terminal experience.

## Design Philosophy
1. **Futuristic/Technical**: Cyan, purple, electric green evoke modern tech aesthetic
2. **High Contrast**: Readable on both dark and light terminal backgrounds
3. **Semantic Colors**: Success=green, Warning=amber, Error=red (universally understood)
4. **Accessibility**: Colors chosen with sufficient contrast ratios
5. **Consistency**: All FastMCP output uses these same colors

## Color Palette

### Primary Colors (Brand Identity)
| Name | Hex | RGB | Purpose |
|------|-----|-----|---------|
| Primary | #00d4ff | (0, 212, 255) | Main brand color, headers, highlights |
| Secondary | #a855f7 | (168, 85, 247) | Accent, keys, important items |
| Accent | #22c55e | (34, 197, 94) | Success indicators, active elements |

### Semantic Colors (Status/Feedback)
| Name | Hex | RGB | Purpose |
|------|-----|-----|---------|
| Success | #22c55e | (34, 197, 94) | Completed, OK, checkmarks |
| Warning | #f59e0b | (245, 158, 11) | Caution, attention needed |
| Error | #ef4444 | (239, 68, 68) | Failures, errors, problems |
| Info | #3b82f6 | (59, 130, 246) | Informational messages |

### Neutral Palette (Text/Backgrounds)
| Name | Hex | RGB | Purpose |
|------|-----|-----|---------|
| Text | #e5e7eb | (229, 231, 235) | Primary text content |
| Text Muted | #9ca3af | (156, 163, 175) | Secondary text, timestamps |
| Text Dim | #6b7280 | (107, 114, 128) | Tertiary text, hints |
| Border | #374151 | (55, 65, 81) | Box borders, dividers |
| Background | #1f2937 | (31, 41, 55) | Panel backgrounds |

## Implementation

### File: crates/fastmcp-console/src/theme.rs

```rust
//\! FastMCP visual theme system.
//\!
//\! Provides a consistent color palette and style definitions
//\! for all rich terminal output throughout FastMCP.

use rich_rust::prelude::*;
use std::sync::OnceLock;

/// The FastMCP color palette and style definitions
pub struct FastMcpTheme {
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Primary Brand Colors
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    /// Vibrant cyan - main brand color
    pub primary: Color,
    /// Soft purple - accent and keys
    pub secondary: Color,
    /// Electric green - success and active
    pub accent: Color,

    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Semantic Colors
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    /// Green - success, completion
    pub success: Color,
    /// Amber - warnings, caution
    pub warning: Color,
    /// Red - errors, failures
    pub error: Color,
    /// Blue - informational
    pub info: Color,

    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Neutral Palette
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    /// Light gray - primary text
    pub text: Color,
    /// Medium gray - secondary text
    pub text_muted: Color,
    /// Dark gray - tertiary text
    pub text_dim: Color,
    /// Border color for boxes/tables
    pub border: Color,
    /// Panel background
    pub background: Color,

    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // Pre-composed Styles
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    /// Style for headers and titles
    pub header_style: Style,
    /// Style for subheaders
    pub subheader_style: Style,
    /// Style for labels/keys
    pub label_style: Style,
    /// Style for values
    pub value_style: Style,
    /// Style for important keys
    pub key_style: Style,
    /// Style for muted/dim text
    pub muted_style: Style,
    /// Style for success messages
    pub success_style: Style,
    /// Style for warning messages
    pub warning_style: Style,
    /// Style for error messages
    pub error_style: Style,
    /// Style for info messages
    pub info_style: Style,
    /// Style for borders
    pub border_style: Style,
}

impl FastMcpTheme {
    /// Create a new theme with FastMCP's default colors
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        // Colors
        let primary = Color::from_rgb(0, 212, 255);
        let secondary = Color::from_rgb(168, 85, 247);
        let accent = Color::from_rgb(34, 197, 94);
        let success = Color::from_rgb(34, 197, 94);
        let warning = Color::from_rgb(245, 158, 11);
        let error = Color::from_rgb(239, 68, 68);
        let info = Color::from_rgb(59, 130, 246);
        let text = Color::from_rgb(229, 231, 235);
        let text_muted = Color::from_rgb(156, 163, 175);
        let text_dim = Color::from_rgb(107, 114, 128);
        let border = Color::from_rgb(55, 65, 81);
        let background = Color::from_rgb(31, 41, 55);

        Self {
            // Colors
            primary: primary.clone(),
            secondary: secondary.clone(),
            accent: accent.clone(),
            success: success.clone(),
            warning: warning.clone(),
            error: error.clone(),
            info: info.clone(),
            text: text.clone(),
            text_muted: text_muted.clone(),
            text_dim: text_dim.clone(),
            border: border.clone(),
            background,

            // Pre-composed styles
            header_style: Style::new().bold().color(primary.clone()),
            subheader_style: Style::new().color(text_muted.clone()),
            label_style: Style::new().color(text_dim.clone()),
            value_style: Style::new().color(text),
            key_style: Style::new().bold().color(secondary),
            muted_style: Style::new().dim().color(text_dim),
            success_style: Style::new().bold().color(success),
            warning_style: Style::new().bold().color(warning),
            error_style: Style::new().bold().color(error),
            info_style: Style::new().color(info),
            border_style: Style::new().color(border),
        }
    }

    /// Get the primary color as a hex string for markup
    pub fn primary_hex(&self) -> String {
        self.primary.hex()
    }

    // Add similar helper methods for other colors...
}

impl Default for FastMcpTheme {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self::new()
    }
}

/// Global theme accessor (lazy initialized)
static THEME: OnceLock<FastMcpTheme> = OnceLock::new();

/// Get the global FastMCP theme
pub fn theme() -> &'static FastMcpTheme {
    THEME.get_or_init(FastMcpTheme::new)
}

/// Set a custom theme (must be called before any output)
pub fn set_theme(theme: FastMcpTheme) -> Result<(), FastMcpTheme> {
    THEME.set(theme)
}
```

## Why These Specific Colors?

### Cyan (#00d4ff) as Primary
- Evokes technology, digital, futuristic
- High visibility on dark backgrounds
- Distinct from standard terminal colors
- Associated with "high performance" in tech branding

### Purple (#a855f7) as Secondary
- Complements cyan beautifully
- Associated with creativity, intelligence
- Makes keys/identifiers stand out
- Popular in modern developer tools

### Green (#22c55e) for Success
- Universal color for "go", "success", "complete"
- Distinct from the primary cyan
- High contrast for visibility

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All colors are defined as Color instances
- [ ] All styles are pre-composed for performance
- [ ] theme() returns a static reference (no allocation per call)
- [ ] Colors work well on both dark and light terminals
- [ ] Helper methods for hex strings are available
- [ ] set_theme() allows customization before first use

